</tr>
</table>
<p>In the mid-8th century, the first <a href="Wind_power" title="Wind power">wind powered</a> automata were built: "statues that turned with the wind over the domes of the four gates and the palace complex of the Round City of <a href="Baghdad" title="Baghdad">Baghdad</a>". The "public spectacle of wind-powered statues had its private counterpart in the '<a href="Abbasid" title="Abbasid" class="mw-redirect">Abbasid</a> palaces where automata of various types were predominantly displayed."<sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup> Also in the 8th century, the <a href="Alchemy_and_chemistry_in_medieval_Islam" title="Alchemy and chemistry in medieval Islam">Muslim alchemist</a>, <a href="J%C4%81bir_ibn_Hayy%C4%81n" title="Jābir ibn Hayyān">Jābir ibn Hayyān</a> (Geber), included recipes for constructing artificial <a href="Snake" title="Snake">snakes</a>, <a href="Scorpion" title="Scorpion">scorpions</a>, and <a href="Human" title="Human">humans</a> which would be subject to their creator's control in his coded <i>Book of Stones</i>. In 827, <a href="Caliph" title="Caliph">Caliph</a> <a href="Al-Ma'mun" title="Al-Ma'mun">Al-Ma'mun</a> had a silver and golden tree in his palace in <a href="Baghdad" title="Baghdad">Baghdad</a>, which had the features of an automatic machine. There were metal birds that sang automatically on the swinging branches of this tree built by <a href="Inventions_of_the_Islamic_Golden_Age" title="Inventions of the Islamic Golden Age" class="mw-redirect">Muslim inventors</a> and <a href="Timeline_of_science_and_engineering_in_the_Islamic_world" title="Timeline of science and engineering in the Islamic world">engineers</a> at the time.<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9"><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup><sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="Wikipedia_Citing_sources" title="Wikipedia:Citing sources"><span title="This citation requires a reference to the specific page or range of pages in which the material appears from January 2012">page&#160;needed</span></a></i>]</sup> The <a href="Abbasid_Caliphate" title="Abbasid Caliphate">Abbasid</a> Caliph <a href="Al-Muqtadir" title="Al-Muqtadir">Al-Muqtadir</a> also had a golden tree in his palace in Baghdad in 915, with birds on it flapping their wings and singing.<sup id="cite_ref-10" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-10"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup> In the 9th century, the <a href="Ban%C5%AB_M%C5%ABs%C4%81" title="Banū Mūsā">Banū Mūsā</a> brothers invented a <a href="Program_(machine)" title="Program (machine)">programmable</a> automatic <a href="Flute" title="Flute">flute</a> player and which they described in their <i><a href="Book_of_Ingenious_Devices" title="Book of Ingenious Devices">Book of Ingenious Devices</a></i>.<sup id="cite_ref-Koetsier_11-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Koetsier-11"><span>[</span>11<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:CIMA_mg_8332.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/CIMA_mg_8332.jpg/220px-CIMA_mg_8332.jpg" width="220" height="330" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/CIMA_mg_8332.jpg/330px-CIMA_mg_8332.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/6e/CIMA_mg_8332.jpg/440px-CIMA_mg_8332.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:CIMA_mg_8332.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf8/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Automaton in the <a href="Centre_International_de_la_M%C3%A9canique_d'Art" title="Centre International de la Mécanique d'Art">Swiss Museum CIMA</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;">
<div class="mediaContainer" style="position:relative;display:block;width:220px"><video id="mwe_player_2" style="width:220px;height:124px" poster="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv/220px--Cima_automaton.ogv.jpg" controls="" preload="none" class="kskin" data-durationhint="81.24" data-startoffset="0" data-mwtitle="Cima_automaton.ogv" data-mwprovider="wikimediacommons"><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv/Cima_automaton.ogv.360p.webm" type="video/webm; codecs=&quot;vp8, vorbis&quot;" transcodekey="360p.webm" data-title="Web streamable WebM (360P)" data-shorttitle="WebM 360P" data-width="640" data-height="360" data-bandwidth="566584" data-framerate="25"></source><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv/Cima_automaton.ogv.480p.webm" type="video/webm; codecs=&quot;vp8, vorbis&quot;" transcodekey="480p.webm" data-title="Web streamable WebM (480P)" data-shorttitle="WebM 480P" data-width="854" data-height="480" data-bandwidth="1075120" data-framerate="25"></source><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv/Cima_automaton.ogv.480p.ogv" type="video/ogg; codecs=&quot;theora, vorbis&quot;" transcodekey="480p.ogv" data-title="Web streamable Ogg video (480P)" data-shorttitle="Ogg 480P" data-width="854" data-height="480" data-bandwidth="1085856" data-framerate="25"></source><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv/Cima_automaton.ogv.720p.webm" type="video/webm; codecs=&quot;vp8, vorbis&quot;" transcodekey="720p.webm" data-title="High quality downloadable WebM (720P)" data-shorttitle="WebM 720P" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-bandwidth="1822640" data-framerate="25"></source><source src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1a/Cima_automaton.ogv" type="video/ogg; codecs=&quot;theora, vorbis&quot;" data-title="Original ogg, 1,280 × 720 (2.3Mbps)" data-shorttitle="Ogg source" data-width="1280" data-height="720" data-bandwidth="2302936" data-framerate="25"></source>Sorry, your browser either has JavaScript disabled or does not have any supported player.<br />
